//! bcinr-core — BranchlessCInRust
//!
//! Academic-grade branchless algorithm library with 12 algorithm families
//! covering mask calculus, integer bitwise, saturation/fixed-point,
//! compare-exchange networks, bitset algebra, byte/word scanning,
//! UTF-8 calculus, parsing primitives, table-driven automata,
//! SWAR reductions, probabilistic sketches, and SIMD primitives.
//!
//! # Design Philosophy
//!
//! The bcinr library is organized into two layers:
//!
//! - **`api/`**: Generated public interface (100% overwritten on sync)
//! - **`logic/`**: Handwritten implementation (bootstrap-once, hand-editable)
//!
//! This separation enables:
//! - Type-safe API contracts enforced at generation time
//! - Hot-reload of the public interface without touching hot loops
//! - Full OTEL instrumentation in the `api/` layer
//! - Unsafe admission policy + opt-in in the `logic/` layer

#![no_std]
#![warn(missing_docs)]

pub mod api;
pub(crate) mod logic;

/// Prelude for convenience imports
pub mod prelude {
    pub use crate::api::*;
}
